Primary Ability Description: "This Pokémon steps on the opposing Pokémon's shadow to prevent it from escaping."
Hidden Ability Description: "Anticipates an ally's attack and dodges it."
Pokedex Entry: It hates light and shock. If attack­ ed, it inflates its body to pump up its counter­ strike.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon's intensely focused, and that protects the Pokémon from flinching."
Secondary Ability Description: "The Pokémon awakens from sleep twice as fast as other Pokémon."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Attack stat if hit by a Grass-type move instead of taking damage."
Pokedex Entry: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent and bite.

Primary Ability Description: "It cannot be knocked out with one hit. One-hit KO moves cannot knock it out, either."
Hidden Ability Description: "Protects the Pokémon from things like sand, hail, and powder."
Pokedex Entry: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn't bother it.

Primary Ability Description: "It cannot be knocked out with one hit. One-hit KO moves cannot knock it out, either."
Hidden Ability Description: "Protects the Pokémon from things like sand, hail, and powder."
Pokedex Entry: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside the armor is a total mystery.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the likelihood of additional effects occurring when attacking."
Secondary Ability Description: "Enables a sure getaway from wild Pokémon."
Hidden Ability Description: "Dark-, Ghost-, and Bug-type moves scare the Pokémon and boost its Speed stat."
Pokedex Entry: When spotted, this POKéMON escapes backward by furi­ ously boring into the ground with its tail.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon's proud of its powerful pincers. They prevent other Pokémon from lowering its Attack stat."
Secondary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness in a sandstorm."
Hidden Ability Description: "The immune system of the Pokémon prevents it from getting poisoned."
Pokedex Entry: It flies straight at its target's face then clamps down on the star­ tled victim to inject poison.

Primary Ability Description: "Protects the Pokémon from recoil damage."
Secondary Ability Description: "It cannot be knocked out with one hit. One-hit KO moves cannot knock it out, either."
Hidden Ability Description: "Removes additional effects to increase the power of moves when attacking."
Pokedex Entry: It is thought its body transformed as a result of iron accumulating internally from swallowing soil.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the power of Rock-, Ground-, and Steel-type moves in a sandstorm."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It is thought its body transformed as a result of iron accumulating internally from swallowing soil.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon intimidates opposing Pokémon upon entering battle, lowering their Attack stat."
Secondary Ability Description: "Enables a sure getaway from wild Pokémon."
Hidden Ability Description: "Dark-, Ghost-, and Bug-type moves scare the Pokémon and boost its Speed stat."
Pokedex Entry: Although it looks frightening, it is actually kind and affectionate. It is very popular among women.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon intimidates opposing Pokémon upon entering battle, lowering their Attack stat."
Secondary Ability Description: "Boosts the Speed stat if the Pokémon has a status condition."
Hidden Ability Description: "Dark-, Ghost-, and Bug-type moves scare the Pokémon and boost its Speed stat."
Pokedex Entry: It is actually timid and easily spooked. If at­ tacked, it flails about to fend off its attacker.

Primary Ability Description: "Contact with the Pokémon may poison the attacker."
Secondary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in rain."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon intimidates opposing Pokémon upon entering battle, lowering their Attack stat."
Pokedex Entry: To fire its poison spikes, it must inflate its body by drinking over 2.6 gallons of water all at once.

Primary Ability Description: "Contact with the Pokémon may poison the attacker."

Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon intimidates opposing Pokémon upon entering battle, lowering their Attack stat."
Pokedex Entry: To fire its poison spikes, it must inflate its body by drinking over 2.6 gallons of water all at once.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Bug-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Halves the Pokémon's weight."
Pokedex Entry: It has a steel-hard body. It intimidates foes by upraising its eye-patterned pincers.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up the Pokémon's weaker moves."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It has a steel-hard body. It intimidates foes by upraising its eye-patterned pincers.

Primary Ability Description: "It cannot be knocked out with one hit. One-hit KO moves cannot knock it out, either."
Secondary Ability Description: "Makes the Pokémon eat a held Berry when its HP drops to half or less, which is sooner than usual."
Hidden Ability Description: "Makes stat changes have an opposite effect."
Pokedex Entry: The BERRIES it stores in its vase-like shell decompose and become a gooey liquid.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Bug-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Secondary Ability Description: "It's so gutsy that having a status condition boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon shows moxie, and that boosts the Attack stat after knocking out any Pokémon."
Pokedex Entry: It is usually docile, but if it is disturbed while sipping honey, it chases off the intruder with its horn.

Primary Ability Description: "Maximizes the number of times multistrike moves hit."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It is usually docile, but if it is disturbed while sipping honey, it chases off the intruder with its horn.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon's intensely focused, and that protects the Pokémon from flinching."
Secondary Ability Description: "Keen eyes prevent other Pokémon from lowering this Pokémon's accuracy."
Hidden Ability Description: "Steals an item from an attacker that made direct contact."
Pokedex Entry: Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked, it sud­ denly extends the claws and startles its enemy.

Secondary Ability Description: "Keen eyes prevent other Pokémon from lowering this Pokémon's accuracy."
Hidden Ability Description: "Steals an item from an attacker that made direct contact."

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon may pick up the item an opposing Pokémon used during a battle. It may pick up items outside of battle, too."
Secondary Ability Description: "Boosts the Speed stat if the Pokémon has a status condition."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon may gather Honey after a battle."
Pokedex Entry: If it finds honey, its crescent mark glows. It always licks its paws because they are soaked with honey.

Primary Ability Description: "It's so gutsy that having a status condition boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat."
Secondary Ability Description: "Boosts the Speed stat if the Pokémon has a status condition."
Hidden Ability Description: "Unnerves opposing Pokémon and makes them unable to eat Berries."
Pokedex Entry: Although it is a good climber, it prefers to snap trees with its forelegs and eat fallen BERRIES.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon is covered with hot magma, which prevents the Pokémon from becoming frozen."
Secondary Ability Description: "Contact with the Pokémon may burn the attacker."
Hidden Ability Description: "Physical attacks to the Pokémon lower its Defense stat but sharply raise its Speed stat."
Pokedex Entry: It never sleeps. It has to keep moving because if it stopped, its magma body would cool and harden.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon is covered with hot magma, which prevents the Pokémon from becoming frozen."
Secondary Ability Description: "Contact with the Pokémon may burn the attacker."
Hidden Ability Description: "Physical attacks to the Pokémon lower its Defense stat but sharply raise its Speed stat."
Pokedex Entry: The shell on its back is just skin that has cooled and hardened. It breaks easily with a slight touch.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon is oblivious, and that keeps it from being infatuated or falling for taunts."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon is protected by a layer of thick fat, which halves the damage taken from Fire- and Ice-type moves."
Pokedex Entry: It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon is oblivious, and that keeps it from being infatuated or falling for taunts."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon is protected by a layer of thick fat, which halves the damage taken from Fire- and Ice-type moves."
Pokedex Entry: Because the long hair all over its body obscures its sight, it just keeps charging repeatedly.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Attack stat, but lowers accuracy."
Secondary Ability Description: "All status conditions heal when the Pokémon switches out."
Hidden Ability Description: "Restores a little HP when withdrawn from battle."
Pokedex Entry: It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure for its beauty.

Primary Ability Description: "Physical attacks to the Pokémon lower its Defense stat but sharply raise its Speed stat."
Hidden Ability Description: "May disable a move used on the Pokémon."
Pokedex Entry: It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure for its beauty.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Attack stat, but lowers accuracy."
Secondary Ability Description: "Powers up moves if they become critical hits when attacking."
Hidden Ability Description: "Raises one stat sharply and lowers another every turn."
Pokedex Entry: It has superb ac­ curacy. The water it shoots out can strike even moving prey from more than 300 feet.

Primary Ability Description: "This Pokémon uses suction cups to stay in one spot to negate all moves and items that force switching out."
Secondary Ability Description: "Powers up moves if they become critical hits when attacking."
Hidden Ability Description: "Raises one stat sharply and lowers another every turn."
Pokedex Entry: It traps enemies with its suction- cupped tentacles then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon is full of vitality, and that prevents it from falling asleep."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon is suffering from insomnia and cannot fall asleep."
Pokedex Entry: It carries food all day long. There are tales about lost people who were saved by the food it had.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in rain."
Secondary Ability Description: "Restores HP if hit by a Water-type move instead of taking damage."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon is covered with a water veil, which prevents the Pokémon from getting a burn."
Pokedex Entry: As it majestically swims, it doesn't care if REMORAID attach to it for scavenging its leftovers.

Primary Ability Description: "Keen eyes prevent other Pokémon from lowering this Pokémon's accuracy."
Secondary Ability Description: "It cannot be knocked out with one hit. One-hit KO moves cannot knock it out, either."
Hidden Ability Description: "Physical attacks to the Pokémon lower its Defense stat but sharply raise its Speed stat."
Pokedex Entry: Its sturdy wings look heavy, but they are actually hollow and light, allowing it to fly freely in the sky.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon awakens from sleep twice as fast as other Pokémon."
Secondary Ability Description: "Powers up the Pokémon's Fire-type moves if it's hit by one."
Hidden Ability Description: "Unnerves opposing Pokémon and makes them unable to eat Berries."
Pokedex Entry: It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing its prey.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon awakens from sleep twice as fast as other Pokémon."
Secondary Ability Description: "Powers up the Pokémon's Fire-type moves if it's hit by one."
Hidden Ability Description: "Unnerves opposing Pokémon and makes them unable to eat Berries."
Pokedex Entry: If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth, the pain will never go away.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Sp. Atk stat in harsh sunlight, but HP decreases every turn."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth, the pain will never go away.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in rain."
Secondary Ability Description: "Powers up moves if they become critical hits when attacking."
Hidden Ability Description: "Prevents the use of explosive moves, such as Self-Destruct, by dampening its surroundings."
Pokedex Entry: It is said that it usually hides in underwater caves. It can create whirlpools by yawning.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon may pick up the item an opposing Pokémon used during a battle. It may pick up items outside of battle, too."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness in a sandstorm."
Pokedex Entry: It swings its long snout around play­ fully, but because it is so strong, that can be dan­ gerous.

Primary Ability Description: "It cannot be knocked out with one hit. One-hit KO moves cannot knock it out, either."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness in a sandstorm."
Pokedex Entry: It has sharp, hard tusks and a rugged hide. Its TACKLE is strong enough to knock down a house.

Primary Ability Description: "When it enters a battle, the Pokémon copies an opposing Pokémon's Ability."
Secondary Ability Description: "Compares an opposing Pokémon's Defense and Sp. Def stats before raising its own Attack or Sp. Atk stat—whichever will be more effective."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts move power when the Pokémon moves last."
Pokedex Entry: This upgraded version of PORYGON is designed for space exploration. It can't fly, though.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon intimidates opposing Pokémon upon entering battle, lowering their Attack stat."
Secondary Ability Description: "When it enters a battle, the Pokémon can check an opposing Pokémon's held item."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Attack stat if hit by a Grass-type move instead of taking damage."
Pokedex Entry: The curved antlers subtly change the flow of air to create a strange space where real­ ity is distorted.

Primary Ability Description: "This Pokémon has its own tempo, and that prevents it from becoming confused."
Hidden Ability Description: "Raises one stat sharply and lowers another every turn."
Pokedex Entry: A special fluid oozes from the tip of its tail. It paints the fluid everywhere to mark its territory.

Primary Ability Description: "It's so gutsy that having a status condition boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat."
Secondary Ability Description: "The Pokémon's determination boosts the Speed stat each time the Pokémon flinches."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon is full of vitality, and that prevents it from falling asleep."
Pokedex Entry: It is always bursting with en­ ergy. To make it­ self stronger, it keeps on fighting even if it loses.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon intimidates opposing Pokémon upon entering battle, lowering their Attack stat."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon's determination boosts the Speed stat each time the Pokémon flinches."
Pokedex Entry: If you become enchanted by its smooth, elegant, dance-like kicks, you may get drilled hard.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon is oblivious, and that keeps it from being infatuated or falling for taunts."
Secondary Ability Description: "When it enters a battle, the Pokémon can tell one of the moves an opposing Pokémon has."
Hidden Ability Description: "Heals status conditions if it's raining."
Pokedex Entry: Its lips are the most sensitive parts on its body. It always uses its lips first to examine things.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon is charged with static electricity, so contact with it may cause paralysis."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon is full of vitality, and that prevents it from falling asleep."
Pokedex Entry: It rotates its arms to generate electricity, but it tires easily, so it charges up only a little bit.

Primary Ability Description: "Contact with the Pokémon may burn the attacker."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon is full of vitality, and that prevents it from falling asleep."
Pokedex Entry: Each and every time it inhales and exhales, hot embers dribble out of its mouth and nostrils.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon is protected by a layer of thick fat, which halves the damage taken from Fire- and Ice-type moves."
Secondary Ability Description: "The Pokémon can hit Ghost-type Pokémon with Normal- and Fighting-type moves."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Attack stat if hit by a Grass-type move instead of taking damage."
Pokedex Entry: Its milk is packed with nutrition, making it the ultimate beverage for the sick or weary.

Primary Ability Description: "All status conditions heal when the Pokémon switches out."
Secondary Ability Description: "Boosts the likelihood of additional effects occurring when attacking."
Hidden Ability Description: "Sometimes heals an ally's status condition."
Pokedex Entry: Anyone who takes even one bite of BLISSEY's egg be­ comes unfailingly caring and pleas­ ant to everyone.

Primary Ability Description: "By putting pressure on the opposing Pokémon, it raises their PP usage."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon's intensely focused, and that protects the Pokémon from flinching."
Pokedex Entry: The rain clouds it carries let it fire thunderbolts at will. They say that it descended with lightning.

Primary Ability Description: "By putting pressure on the opposing Pokémon, it raises their PP usage."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon's intensely focused, and that protects the Pokémon from flinching."
Pokedex Entry: Volcanoes erupt when it barks. Un­ able to restrain its extreme power, it races headlong around the land.

Primary Ability Description: "By putting pressure on the opposing Pokémon, it raises their PP usage."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon's intensely focused, and that protects the Pokémon from flinching."
Pokedex Entry: It races around the world to purify fouled water. It dashes away with the north wind.

Primary Ability Description: "It's so gutsy that having a status condition boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness in a sandstorm."
Pokedex Entry: It feeds on soil. After it has eaten a large mountain, it will fall asleep so it can grow.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon may heal its own status conditions by shedding its skin."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Its shell is as hard as sheet rock, and it is also very strong. Its THRASHING can topple a mountain.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon summons a sandstorm when it enters a battle."
Hidden Ability Description: "Unnerves opposing Pokémon and makes them unable to eat Berries."
Pokedex Entry: Its body can't be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon summons a sandstorm when it enters a battle."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Its body can't be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.

Primary Ability Description: "By putting pressure on the opposing Pokémon, it raises their PP usage."
Hidden Ability Description: "Reduces the amount of damage the Pokémon takes while its HP is full."
Pokedex Entry: It is said that it quietly spends its time deep at the bottom of the sea because its powers are too strong.

Primary Ability Description: "By putting pressure on the opposing Pokémon, it raises their PP usage."
Hidden Ability Description: "Restores a little HP when withdrawn from battle."
Pokedex Entry: Legends claim this POKéMON flies the world's skies con­ tinuously on its magnificent seven- colored wings.

Primary Ability Description: "All status conditions heal when the Pokémon switches out."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: This POKéMON wan­ ders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Grass-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Speed stat if the Pokémon's held item is used or lost."
Pokedex Entry: TREECKO has small hooks on the bottom of its feet that enable it to scale vertical walls. This POKéMON attacks by slamming foes with its thick tail.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Grass-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Speed stat if the Pokémon's held item is used or lost."
Pokedex Entry: The leaves growing out of GROVYLE’s body are convenient for camouflaging it from enemies in the forest. This POKéMON is a master at climbing trees in jungles.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Grass-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Speed stat if the Pokémon's held item is used or lost."
Pokedex Entry: The leaves growing on SCEPTILE’s body are very sharp edged. This POKéMON is very agile - it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.

Pokedex Entry: The leaves growing on SCEPTILE’s body are very sharp edged. This POKéMON is very agile - it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Fire-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Its Speed stat is boosted every turn."
Pokedex Entry: TORCHIC sticks with its TRAINER, following behind with unsteady steps. This POKéMON breathes fire of over 1,800 degrees F, including fireballs that leave the foe scorched black.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Fire-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Its Speed stat is boosted every turn."
Pokedex Entry: COMBUSKEN toughens up its legs and thighs by running through fields and mountains. This POKéMON’s legs possess both speed and power, enabling it to dole out ten kicks in one second.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Fire-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Its Speed stat is boosted every turn."
Pokedex Entry: In battle, BLAZIKEN blows out intense flames from its wrists and attacks foes courageously. The stronger the foe, the more intensely this POKéMON’s wrists burn.

Pokedex Entry: In battle, BLAZIKEN blows out intense flames from its wrists and attacks foes courageously. The stronger the foe, the more intensely this POKéMON’s wrists burn.

Hidden Ability Description: "Prevents the use of explosive moves, such as Self-Destruct, by dampening its surroundings."
Pokedex Entry: The fin on MUDKIP’s head acts as highly sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense movements of water and air, this POKéMON can determine what is taking place around it without using its eyes.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Water-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Prevents the use of explosive moves, such as Self-Destruct, by dampening its surroundings."
Pokedex Entry: The surface of MARSHTOMP’s body is enveloped by a thin, sticky film that enables it to live on land. This POKéMON plays in mud on beaches when the ocean tide is low.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Water-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Prevents the use of explosive moves, such as Self-Destruct, by dampening its surroundings."
Pokedex Entry: SWAMPERT is very strong. It has enough power to easily drag a boulder weighing more than a ton. This POKéMON also has powerful vision that lets it see even in murky water.

Secondary Ability Description: "Boosts the Speed stat if the Pokémon has a status condition."
Hidden Ability Description: "Dark-, Ghost-, and Bug-type moves scare the Pokémon and boost its Speed stat."
Pokedex Entry: At first sight, POOCHYENA takes a bite at anything that moves. This POKéMON chases after prey until the victim becomes exhausted. However, it may turn tail if the prey strikes back.

Pokedex Entry: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

Primary Ability Description: "Gives priority to a status move."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat sharply when its stats are lowered."
Pokedex Entry: Countless charred remains mar the landscape of places through which Thundurus has passed.

Pokedex Entry: Countless charred remains mar the landscape of places through which Thundurus has passed.

Primary Ability Description: "Moves can be used on the target regardless of its Abilities."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.

Primary Ability Description: "Moves can be used on the target regardless of its Abilities."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the power of Rock-, Ground-, and Steel-type moves in a sandstorm."
Hidden Ability Description: "Removes additional effects to increase the power of moves when attacking."
Pokedex Entry: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.”

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon intimidates opposing Pokémon upon entering battle, lowering their Attack stat."

Pokedex Entry: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.”

Primary Ability Description: "By putting pressure on the opposing Pokémon, it raises their PP usage."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

Primary Ability Description: "Being hit by a Dark-type move boosts the Attack stat of the Pokémon, for justice."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: By blasting water from its hooves, it can glide across water. It excels at using leg moves while battling.

Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: By blasting water from its hooves, it can glide across water. It excels at using leg moves while battling.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the likelihood of additional effects occurring when attacking."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the likelihood of additional effects occurring when attacking."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

Primary Ability Description: "Compares an opposing Pokémon's Defense and Sp. Def stats before raising its own Attack or Sp. Atk stat—whichever will be more effective."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Over 300 million years ago, it was feared as the strongest of hunters. It has been modified by Team Plasma.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Grass-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Protects the Pokémon from some ball and bomb moves."
Pokedex Entry: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Grass-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Protects the Pokémon from some ball and bomb moves."
Pokedex Entry: It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predators’ attacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Grass-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Protects the Pokémon from some ball and bomb moves."
Pokedex Entry: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank. It shields its allies from danger with its own body.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Fire-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon steals the held item of a Pokémon it hits with a move."
Pokedex Entry: Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Fire-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon steals the held item of a Pokémon it hits with a move."
Pokedex Entry: It has a twig stuck in its tail. With friction from its tail fur, it sets the twig on fire and launches into battle.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Fire-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon steals the held item of a Pokémon it hits with a move."
Pokedex Entry: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Water-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Changes the Pokémon's type to the type of the move it's about to use."
Pokedex Entry: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Water-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Changes the Pokémon's type to the type of the move it's about to use."
Pokedex Entry: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Water-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Changes the Pokémon's type to the type of the move it's about to use."
Special Event Ability Description: "When the Pokémon knocks out a target, its bond with its Trainer is strengthened, and its Attack, Sp. Atk, and Speed stats are boosted."
Pokedex Entry: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

Primary Ability Description: "When the Pokémon knocks out a target, its bond with its Trainer is strengthened, and its Attack, Sp. Atk, and Speed stats are boosted."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon may pick up the item an opposing Pokémon used during a battle. It may pick up items outside of battle, too."
Secondary Ability Description: "Restores HP as well when the Pokémon eats a Berry."
Hidden Ability Description: "Doubles the Pokémon's Attack stat."
Pokedex Entry: They use their large ears to dig burrows. They will dig the whole night through.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon may pick up the item an opposing Pokémon used during a battle. It may pick up items outside of battle, too."
Secondary Ability Description: "Restores HP as well when the Pokémon eats a Berry."
Hidden Ability Description: "Doubles the Pokémon's Attack stat."
Pokedex Entry: With their powerful ears, they can heft boulders of a ton or more with ease. They can be a big help at construction sites.

Primary Ability Description: "Protects the Pokémon from Defense-lowering effects."
Hidden Ability Description: "Gives priority to Flying-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is full."
Pokedex Entry: These friendly Pokémon send signals to one another with beautiful chirps and tail-feather movements.

Primary Ability Description: "Contact with the Pokémon may burn the attacker."
Hidden Ability Description: "Gives priority to Flying-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is full."
Pokedex Entry: From its beak, it expels embers that set the tall grass on fire. Then it pounces on the bewildered prey that pop out of the grass.

Primary Ability Description: "Contact with the Pokémon may burn the attacker."
Hidden Ability Description: "Gives priority to Flying-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is full."
Pokedex Entry: In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.

Primary Ability Description: "This Pokémon's dust blocks the additional effects of attacks taken."
Secondary Ability Description: "The Pokémon's compound eyes boost its accuracy."
Hidden Ability Description: "Reduces damage done to allies."
Pokedex Entry: When under attack from bird Pokémon, it spews a poisonous black powder that causes paralysis on contact.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon may heal its own status conditions by shedding its skin."
Hidden Ability Description: "Reduces damage done to allies."
Pokedex Entry: It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.

Primary Ability Description: "This Pokémon's dust blocks the additional effects of attacks taken."
Secondary Ability Description: "The Pokémon's compound eyes boost its accuracy."
Hidden Ability Description: "Reduces damage done to allies."
Pokedex Entry: Vivillon with many different patterns are found all over the world. These patterns are affected by the climate of their habitat.

Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon shows moxie, and that boosts the Attack stat after knocking out any Pokémon."
Pokedex Entry: The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Attack stat if hit by a Grass-type move instead of taking damage."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Defense stat on Grassy Terrain."
Pokedex Entry: Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Attack stat if hit by a Grass-type move instead of taking damage."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Defense stat on Grassy Terrain."
Pokedex Entry: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up punching moves."
Secondary Ability Description: "Moves can be used on the target regardless of its Abilities."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon can hit Ghost-type Pokémon with Normal- and Fighting-type moves."
Pokedex Entry: It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies, but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating. Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up punching moves."
Secondary Ability Description: "Moves can be used on the target regardless of its Abilities."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon can hit Ghost-type Pokémon with Normal- and Fighting-type moves."
Pokedex Entry: Although it possesses a violent temperament, it won’t put up with bullying. It uses the leaf in its mouth to sense the movements of its enemies.

Primary Ability Description: "Keen eyes prevent other Pokémon from lowering this Pokémon's accuracy."
Secondary Ability Description: "Passes through the opposing Pokémon's barrier, substitute, and the like and strikes."
Hidden Ability Description: "This Pokémon has its own tempo, and that prevents it from becoming confused."
Pokedex Entry: The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.

Primary Ability Description: "Keen eyes prevent other Pokémon from lowering this Pokémon's accuracy."
Secondary Ability Description: "Passes through the opposing Pokémon's barrier, substitute, and the like and strikes."
Hidden Ability Description: "Gives priority to a status move."
Pokedex Entry: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.

Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Sp. Atk stat sharply when a stat is lowered."
Pokedex Entry: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon employs no-guard tactics to ensure incoming and outgoing attacks always land."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon employs no-guard tactics to ensure incoming and outgoing attacks always land."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords, which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacks and slash their enemies to ribbons.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon changes its form to Blade Forme when it uses an attack move and changes to Shield Forme when it uses King's Shield."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Generations of kings were attended by these Pokémon, which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and Pokémon.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon changes its form to Blade Forme when it uses an attack move and changes to Shield Forme when it uses King's Shield."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Generations of kings were attended by these Pokémon, which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and Pokémon.

Primary Ability Description: "Sometimes heals an ally's status condition."
Hidden Ability Description: "Protects itself and its allies from attacks that limit their move choices."
Pokedex Entry: It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. This fragrance changes depending on what it has eaten.

Primary Ability Description: "Sometimes heals an ally's status condition."
Hidden Ability Description: "Protects itself and its allies from attacks that limit their move choices."
Pokedex Entry: It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.

Primary Ability Description: "Prevents itself and ally Pokémon from falling asleep."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Speed stat if the Pokémon's held item is used or lost."
Pokedex Entry: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.

Primary Ability Description: "Prevents itself and ally Pokémon from falling asleep."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Speed stat if the Pokémon's held item is used or lost."
Pokedex Entry: It can distinguish the faintest of scents. It puts its sensitive sense of smell to use by helping pastry chefs in their work.

Primary Ability Description: "This Pokémon uses suction cups to stay in one spot to negate all moves and items that force switching out."
Secondary Ability Description: "Makes stat changes have an opposite effect."
Hidden Ability Description: "Passes through the opposing Pokémon's barrier, substitute, and the like and strikes."
Pokedex Entry: Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.

Primary Ability Description: "This Pokémon uses suction cups to stay in one spot to negate all moves and items that force switching out."
Secondary Ability Description: "Makes stat changes have an opposite effect."
Hidden Ability Description: "Passes through the opposing Pokémon's barrier, substitute, and the like and strikes."
Pokedex Entry: It wields the most compelling hypnotic powers of any Pokémon, and it forces others to do whatever it wants.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up moves that make direct contact."
Secondary Ability Description: "Powers up moves if they become critical hits when attacking."
Hidden Ability Description: "Steals an item from an attacker that made direct contact."
Pokedex Entry: Two Binacle live together on one rock. When they fight, one of them will move to a different rock.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up moves that make direct contact."
Secondary Ability Description: "Powers up moves if they become critical hits when attacking."
Hidden Ability Description: "Steals an item from an attacker that made direct contact."
Pokedex Entry: When they evolve, two Binacle multiply into seven. They fight with the power of seven Binacle.

Primary Ability Description: "Contact with the Pokémon may poison the attacker."
Secondary Ability Description: "May poison a target when the Pokémon makes contact."
Hidden Ability Description: "Powers up moves of the same type as the Pokémon."
Pokedex Entry: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.

Primary Ability Description: "Contact with the Pokémon may poison the attacker."
Secondary Ability Description: "May poison a target when the Pokémon makes contact."
Hidden Ability Description: "Powers up moves of the same type as the Pokémon."
Pokedex Entry: Their poison is strong enough to eat through the hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminately at anything that enters their territory.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up aura and pulse moves."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: They knock down flying prey by firing compressed water from their massive claws like shooting a pistol.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up aura and pulse moves."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Their enormous claws launch cannonballs of water powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.

Primary Ability Description: "Restores HP in rain or when hit by Water-type moves. Reduces HP in harsh sunlight, and increases the damage received from Fire-type moves."
Secondary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness in a sandstorm."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Sp. Atk stat in harsh sunlight, but HP decreases every turn."
Pokedex Entry: They make their home in deserts. They can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.

Primary Ability Description: "Restores HP in rain or when hit by Water-type moves. Reduces HP in harsh sunlight, and increases the damage received from Fire-type moves."

Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon makes it snow when it enters a battle."

Primary Ability Description: "Prevents status conditions in harsh sunlight."
Secondary Ability Description: "The Pokémon is oblivious, and that keeps it from being infatuated or falling for taunts."
Hidden Ability Description: "Prevents itself and ally Pokémon from falling asleep."
Pokedex Entry: A delectable aroma pours from its body. They are often swallowed whole by Toucannon lured by that wafting deliciousness.

Primary Ability Description: "Prevents status conditions in harsh sunlight."
Secondary Ability Description: "The Pokémon is oblivious, and that keeps it from being infatuated or falling for taunts."
Hidden Ability Description: "Prevents itself and ally Pokémon from falling asleep."
Pokedex Entry: The sepals on its head developed to protect its body. These are quite hard, so even if pecked by bird Pokémon, this Pokémon is totally fine.

Primary Ability Description: "Prevents status conditions in harsh sunlight."
Secondary Ability Description: "Its majesty pressures the opposing Pokémon, making it unable to attack using priority moves."
Hidden Ability Description: "Prevents itself and ally Pokémon from falling asleep."
Pokedex Entry: Its long, striking legs aren’t just for show but to be used to kick with skill. In victory, it shows off by kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.

Primary Ability Description: "Ally Grass-type Pokémon are protected from status conditions and the lowering of their stats."
Hidden Ability Description: "All status conditions heal when the Pokémon switches out."
Pokedex Entry: It attaches flowers to its highly nutritious vine. This revitalizes the flowers, and they give off an aromatic scent.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon's intensely focused, and that protects the Pokémon from flinching."
Secondary Ability Description: "Anticipates an ally's attack and dodges it."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon passes its item to an ally that has used up an item."
Pokedex Entry: Known for its extreme intelligence, this Pokémon will look down on inexperienced Trainers, so it’s best suited to veteran Trainers.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon copies the Ability of a defeated ally."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat sharply when its stats are lowered."
Pokedex Entry: They form groups of roughly 20 individuals. Their mutual bond is remarkable—they will never let down a comrade.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon cowardly switches out when its HP becomes half or less."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon is a coward. As it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves a sparkling clean path in its wake.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon, sensing danger, switches out when its HP becomes half or less."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: With a flashing slash of its giant sharp claws, it cleaves seawater—or even air—right in two.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Defense stat sharply when hit by a Water-type move."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness in a sandstorm."
Pokedex Entry: Born from a sand mound playfully built by a child, this Pokémon embodies the grudges of the departed.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Defense stat sharply when hit by a Water-type move."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness in a sandstorm."
Pokedex Entry: Possessed people controlled by this Pokémon transformed its sand mound into a castle. As it evolved, its power to curse grew ever stronger.

Primary Ability Description: "Damages the attacker landing the finishing hit by the amount equal to its last HP."
Hidden Ability Description: "When attacking, the Pokémon ignores the target Pokémon's stat changes."
Pokedex Entry: It’s covered in a slime that keeps its skin moist, allowing it to stay on land for days without drying up.

Primary Ability Description: "Hard armor protects the Pokémon from critical hits."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: The heavy control mask it wears suppresses its intrinsic capabilities. This Pokémon has some hidden special power.

Primary Ability Description: "Changes the Pokémon's type to match the memory disc it holds."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Its trust in its partner is what awakens it. This Pokémon is capable of changing its type, a flexibility that is well displayed in battle.

Primary Ability Description: "When its HP becomes half or less, the Pokémon's shell breaks and it becomes aggressive."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Originally making its home in the ozone layer, it hurtles to the ground when the shell enclosing its body grows too heavy.

Primary Ability Description: "It's always drowsing and will never wake up. It can attack without waking up."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It is born asleep, and it dies asleep. All its movements are apparently no more than the results of it tossing and turning in its dreams.

Primary Ability Description: "A hard shell protects the Pokémon from critical hits."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: The shell on its back is chemically unstable and explodes violently if struck. The hole in its stomach is its weak point.

Primary Ability Description: "Inflicts damage on the attacker upon contact with iron barbs."
Secondary Ability Description: "The Pokémon draws in all Electric-type moves. Instead of being hit by Electric-type moves, it boosts its Sp. Atk."
Hidden Ability Description: "It cannot be knocked out with one hit. One-hit KO moves cannot knock it out, either."
Pokedex Entry: The spiny fur on its back is normally at rest. When this Pokémon becomes agitated, its fur stands on end and stabs into its attackers.

Primary Ability Description: "Once per battle, the shroud that covers the Pokémon can protect it from an attack."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholar who saw what was under its rag was overwhelmed by terror and died from the shock.

Primary Ability Description: "Surprises the opposing Pokémon, making it unable to attack using priority moves."
Secondary Ability Description: "The Pokémon's strong jaw boosts the power of its biting moves."
Hidden Ability Description: "Makes status moves more likely to miss."
Pokedex Entry: When it unleashes its psychic power from the protuberance on its head, the grating sound of grinding teeth echoes through the area.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Sp. Atk stat when it takes a hit that causes its HP to become half or less."
Secondary Ability Description: "Boosts the Attack stat if hit by a Grass-type move instead of taking damage."
Hidden Ability Description: "Eliminates the effects of weather."
Pokedex Entry: It has a compassionate personality, but if it is angered, it completely destroys its surroundings with its intense breath.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Steel-type moves."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Swinging its massive anchor, it can KO Wailord in a single blow. What appears to be green seaweed is actually its body.

Primary Ability Description: "Protects the Pokémon from some ball and bomb moves."
Secondary Ability Description: "Soundproofing gives the Pokémon full immunity to all sound-based moves."
Hidden Ability Description: "Protects the Pokémon from things like sand, hail, and powder."
Pokedex Entry: It expresses its feelings by smacking its scales. Metallic sounds echo through the tall mountains where Jangmo-o lives.

Primary Ability Description: "Protects the Pokémon from some ball and bomb moves."
Secondary Ability Description: "Soundproofing gives the Pokémon full immunity to all sound-based moves."
Hidden Ability Description: "Protects the Pokémon from things like sand, hail, and powder."
Pokedex Entry: It leaps at its prey with a courageous shout. Its scaly punches tear its opponents to shreds.

Primary Ability Description: "Protects the Pokémon from some ball and bomb moves."
Secondary Ability Description: "Soundproofing gives the Pokémon full immunity to all sound-based moves."
Hidden Ability Description: "Protects the Pokémon from things like sand, hail, and powder."
Pokedex Entry: When it spots enemies, it threatens them by jingling the scales on its tail. Weak opponents will crack and flee in panic.

Primary Ability Description: "Turns the ground into Electric Terrain when the Pokémon enters a battle."
Hidden Ability Description: "Anticipates an ally's attack and dodges it."
Pokedex Entry: This guardian deity of Melemele is brimming with curiosity. It summons thunderclouds and stores their lightning inside its body.

Primary Ability Description: "Turns the ground into Psychic Terrain when the Pokémon enters a battle."
Hidden Ability Description: "Anticipates an ally's attack and dodges it."
Pokedex Entry: This guardian deity of Akala is guilelessly cruel. The fragrant aroma of flowers is the source of its energy.

Primary Ability Description: "Turns the ground into Grassy Terrain when the Pokémon enters a battle."
Hidden Ability Description: "Anticipates an ally's attack and dodges it."
Pokedex Entry: It pulls large trees up by the roots and swings them around. It causes vegetation to grow, and then it absorbs energy from the growth.

Primary Ability Description: "Turns the ground into Misty Terrain when the Pokémon enters a battle."
Hidden Ability Description: "Anticipates an ally's attack and dodges it."
Pokedex Entry: The dense fog it creates brings the downfall and destruction of its confused enemies. Ocean currents are the source of its energy.

Primary Ability Description: "When attacking, the Pokémon ignores the target Pokémon's stat changes."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Its body is gaseous and frail. It slowly grows as it collects dust from the atmosphere.

Primary Ability Description: "It cannot be knocked out with one hit. One-hit KO moves cannot knock it out, either."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Motionless as if dead, its body is faintly warm to the touch. In the distant past, it was called the cocoon of the stars.

Primary Ability Description: "Prevents other Pokémon's moves or Abilities from lowering the Pokémon's stats."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It is said to live in another world. The intense light it radiates from the surface of its body can make the darkest of nights light up like midday.

Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It is said to be a female evolution of Cosmog. When its third eye activates, away it flies to another world.

Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: One of several mysterious Ultra Beasts. People on the street report observing those infested by it suddenly becoming violent.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon boosts its most proficient stat each time it knocks out a Pokémon."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: This Ultra Beast appeared from another world. It shows off its body, but whether that display is a boast or a threat remains unclear.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon boosts its most proficient stat each time it knocks out a Pokémon."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: One of the dangerous Ultra Beasts, it has been spotted running across the land at terrific speeds.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon boosts its most proficient stat each time it knocks out a Pokémon."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: One of the mysterious life-forms known as Ultra Beasts. Astonishing electric shocks emanate from its entire body, according to witnesses.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon boosts its most proficient stat each time it knocks out a Pokémon."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. Witnesses observed it flying across the sky at high speed.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon boosts its most proficient stat each time it knocks out a Pokémon."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: This Ultra Beast came from the Ultra Wormhole. It seems not to attack enemies on its own, but its sharp body is a dangerous weapon in itself.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon boosts its most proficient stat each time it knocks out a Pokémon."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It has gobbled mountains and swallowed whole buildings, according to reports. It’s one of the Ultra Beasts.

Primary Ability Description: "Reduces the power of supereffective attacks taken."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Reminiscent of the Ultra Beasts, this life-form, apparently asleep underground, is thought to have come from another world in ancient times.

Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Reminiscent of the Ultra Beasts, this life-form, apparently asleep underground, is thought to have come from another world in ancient times.

Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: This artificial Pokémon, constructed more than 500 years ago, can understand human speech but cannot itself speak.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts its Sp. Atk stat every time a Pokémon faints."

Pokedex Entry: This artificial Pokémon, constructed more than 500 years ago, can understand human speech but cannot itself speak.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up the Pokémon's weaker moves."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Able to conceal itself in shadows, it never appears before humans, so its very existence was the stuff of myth.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon boosts its most proficient stat each time it knocks out a Pokémon."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon boosts its most proficient stat each time it knocks out a Pokémon."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid inside its body. It is one of the organisms known as UBs.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon boosts its most proficient stat each time it knocks out a Pokémon."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon boosts its most proficient stat each time it knocks out a Pokémon."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It’s apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

Primary Ability Description: "Restores HP if hit by an Electric-type move instead of taking damage."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they’ll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.

Primary Ability Description: "Prevents Steel-type Pokémon from escaping using its magnetic force."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up punching moves."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up punching moves."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Grass-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Turns the ground into Grassy Terrain when the Pokémon enters a battle."
Pokedex Entry: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Grass-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Turns the ground into Grassy Terrain when the Pokémon enters a battle."
Pokedex Entry: The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Grass-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Turns the ground into Grassy Terrain when the Pokémon enters a battle."
Pokedex Entry: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Grass-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Turns the ground into Grassy Terrain when the Pokémon enters a battle."
Pokedex Entry: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Fire-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Changes the Pokémon's type to the type of the move it's about to use."
Pokedex Entry: A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokémon’s body. Once that happens, it’s ready to fight at full power.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Fire-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Changes the Pokémon's type to the type of the move it's about to use."
Pokedex Entry: Its thick and fluffy fur protects it from the cold and enables it to use hotter fire moves.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Fire-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Changes the Pokémon's type to the type of the move it's about to use."
Pokedex Entry: It juggles a pebble with its feet, turning it into a burning soccer ball. Its shots strike opponents hard and leave them scorched.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Fire-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Changes the Pokémon's type to the type of the move it's about to use."
Pokedex Entry: It juggles a pebble with its feet, turning it into a burning soccer ball. Its shots strike opponents hard and leave them scorched.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Water-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Powers up moves if they become critical hits when attacking."
Pokedex Entry: When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won’t be able to resist weeping.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Water-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Powers up moves if they become critical hits when attacking."
Pokedex Entry: A clever combatant, this Pokémon battles using water balloons created with moisture secreted from its palms.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Water-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Powers up moves if they become critical hits when attacking."
Pokedex Entry: It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Water-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Hidden Ability Description: "Powers up moves if they become critical hits when attacking."
Pokedex Entry: It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.

Primary Ability Description: "Restores HP as well when the Pokémon eats a Berry."
Hidden Ability Description: "Makes the Pokémon eat a held Berry when its HP drops to half or less, which is sooner than usual."
Pokedex Entry: Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.

Primary Ability Description: "Restores HP as well when the Pokémon eats a Berry."
Hidden Ability Description: "Makes the Pokémon eat a held Berry when its HP drops to half or less, which is sooner than usual."
Pokedex Entry: It stashes berries in its tail—so many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokémon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn’t notice the loss.

Primary Ability Description: "Keen eyes prevent other Pokémon from lowering this Pokémon's accuracy."
Secondary Ability Description: "Unnerves opposing Pokémon and makes them unable to eat Berries."
Hidden Ability Description: "Protects the Pokémon from Defense-lowering effects."
Pokedex Entry: It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokémon benefits from every battle—even a defeat increases its strength a bit.

Primary Ability Description: "Keen eyes prevent other Pokémon from lowering this Pokémon's accuracy."
Secondary Ability Description: "Unnerves opposing Pokémon and makes them unable to eat Berries."
Hidden Ability Description: "Protects the Pokémon from Defense-lowering effects."
Pokedex Entry: Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokémon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies.

Primary Ability Description: "By putting pressure on the opposing Pokémon, it raises their PP usage."
Secondary Ability Description: "Unnerves opposing Pokémon and makes them unable to eat Berries."
Hidden Ability Description: "Bounces back only the stat-lowering effects that the Pokémon receives."
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.

Primary Ability Description: "By putting pressure on the opposing Pokémon, it raises their PP usage."
Secondary Ability Description: "Unnerves opposing Pokémon and makes them unable to eat Berries."
Hidden Ability Description: "Bounces back only the stat-lowering effects that the Pokémon receives."
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Bug-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Secondary Ability Description: "The Pokémon's compound eyes boost its accuracy."
Hidden Ability Description: "Anticipates an ally's attack and dodges it."
Pokedex Entry: A constant collector of information, this Pokémon is very smart. Very strong is what it isn’t.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Bug-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Secondary Ability Description: "The Pokémon's compound eyes boost its accuracy."
Hidden Ability Description: "Anticipates an ally's attack and dodges it."
Pokedex Entry: It barely moves, but it’s still alive. Hiding in its shell without food or water seems to have awakened its psychic powers.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Bug-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Secondary Ability Description: "When it enters a battle, the Pokémon can check an opposing Pokémon's held item."
Hidden Ability Description: "Anticipates an ally's attack and dodges it."
Pokedex Entry: It’s famous for its high level of intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power.

Primary Ability Description: "Powers up Bug-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low."
Secondary Ability Description: "When it enters a battle, the Pokémon can check an opposing Pokémon's held item."
Hidden Ability Description: "Anticipates an ally's attack and dodges it."
Pokedex Entry: It’s famous for its high level of intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power.

Primary Ability Description: "Enables a sure getaway from wild Pokémon."
Secondary Ability Description: "Boosts the Speed stat if the Pokémon's held item is used or lost."
Hidden Ability Description: "Doubles the damage dealt to the target's replacement if the target switches out."
Pokedex Entry: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.

Primary Ability Description: "Enables a sure getaway from wild Pokémon."
Secondary Ability Description: "Boosts the Speed stat if the Pokémon's held item is used or lost."
Hidden Ability Description: "Doubles the damage dealt to the target's replacement if the target switches out."
Pokedex Entry: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.

Primary Ability Description: "When the Pokémon is hit by an attack, it scatters cotton fluff around and lowers the Speed stat of all Pokémon except itself."
Secondary Ability Description: "Restores a little HP when withdrawn from battle."
Hidden Ability Description: "Contact with the Pokémon may inflict poison, sleep, or paralysis on its attacker."
Pokedex Entry: It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg, then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly.

Primary Ability Description: "When the Pokémon is hit by an attack, it scatters cotton fluff around and lowers the Speed stat of all Pokémon except itself."
Secondary Ability Description: "Restores a little HP when withdrawn from battle."
Hidden Ability Description: "Contact with the Pokémon may inflict poison, sleep, or paralysis on its attacker."
Pokedex Entry: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokémon can benefit from them.

Primary Ability Description: "Halves the damage taken from moves that make direct contact, but doubles that of Fire-type moves."
Secondary Ability Description: "Enables a sure getaway from wild Pokémon."
Hidden Ability Description: "Protects the Pokémon from some ball and bomb moves."
Pokedex Entry: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.

Primary Ability Description: "Halves the damage taken from moves that make direct contact, but doubles that of Fire-type moves."
Secondary Ability Description: "The Pokémon's determination boosts the Speed stat each time the Pokémon flinches."
Hidden Ability Description: "Protects the Pokémon from some ball and bomb moves."
Pokedex Entry: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You’ll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon's strong jaw boosts the power of its biting moves."
Secondary Ability Description: "A hard shell protects the Pokémon from critical hits."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in rain."
Pokedex Entry: Apparently the itch of its teething impels it to snap its jaws at anything in front of it.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon's strong jaw boosts the power of its biting moves."
Secondary Ability Description: "A hard shell protects the Pokémon from critical hits."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in rain."
Pokedex Entry: With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokémon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon's strong jaw boosts the power of its biting moves."
Secondary Ability Description: "A hard shell protects the Pokémon from critical hits."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in rain."
Pokedex Entry: With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokémon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.

Primary Ability Description: "If the Pokémon is not holding an item, it will fetch the Poke Ball from the first failed throw of the battle."
Hidden Ability Description: "Dark-, Ghost-, and Bug-type moves scare the Pokémon and boost its Speed stat."
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon's strong jaw boosts the power of its biting moves."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Sp. Atk stat sharply when a stat is lowered."
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat drastically if hit by a Fire- or Water-type move."
Secondary Ability Description: "The heatproof body of the Pokémon halves the damage from Fire-type moves that hit it."
Hidden Ability Description: "Powers up the Pokémon's Fire-type moves if it's hit by one."
Pokedex Entry: Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokémon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat drastically if hit by a Fire- or Water-type move."
Secondary Ability Description: "Contact with the Pokémon may burn the attacker."
Hidden Ability Description: "Powers up the Pokémon's Fire-type moves if it's hit by one."
Pokedex Entry: It forms coal inside its body. Coal dropped by this Pokémon once helped fuel the lives of people in the Galar region.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat drastically if hit by a Fire- or Water-type move."
Secondary Ability Description: "Contact with the Pokémon may burn the attacker."
Hidden Ability Description: "Powers up the Pokémon's Fire-type moves if it's hit by one."
Pokedex Entry: It’s usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat drastically if hit by a Fire- or Water-type move."
Secondary Ability Description: "Contact with the Pokémon may burn the attacker."

Pokedex Entry: It will open the branches of its head to envelop its prey. Once it absorbs all the life energy it needs, it expels the prey and discards it.

Pokedex Entry: When attacked, this Pokémon will wield the tendrils on its body like fists and pelt the opponent with a storm of punches.

Primary Ability Description: "Scatters poison spikes at the feet of the opposing team when the Pokémon takes damage from physical moves."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon can poison the target even if it's a Steel or Poison type."
Pokedex Entry: It absorbs nutrients from cave walls. The petals it wears are made of crystallized poison.

Primary Ability Description: "Scatters poison spikes at the feet of the opposing team when the Pokémon takes damage from physical moves."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon can poison the target even if it's a Steel or Poison type."
Pokedex Entry: When this Pokémon detects danger, it will open up its crystalline petals and fire beams from its conical body.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon may pick up the item an opposing Pokémon used during a battle. It may pick up items outside of battle, too."
Hidden Ability Description: "Halves the damage taken from moves that make direct contact, but doubles that of Fire-type moves."
Pokedex Entry: It is said that a dog Pokémon that died in the wild without ever interacting with a human was reborn as this Pokémon.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in a sandstorm."
Hidden Ability Description: "Halves the damage taken from moves that make direct contact, but doubles that of Fire-type moves."
Pokedex Entry: Houndstone spends most of its time sleeping in graveyards. Among all the dog Pokémon, this one is most loyal to its master.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon can hit Ghost-type Pokémon with Normal- and Fighting-type moves."
Secondary Ability Description: "Raises evasiveness if the Pokémon is confused."
Hidden Ability Description: "When the Pokémon enters a battle, it copies an ally's stat changes."
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon apparently ties the base of its neck into a knot so that energy stored in its belly does not escape from its beak.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon is protected by a layer of thick fat, which halves the damage taken from Fire- and Ice-type moves."
Hidden Ability Description: "Removes additional effects to increase the power of moves when attacking."
Pokedex Entry: This species left the ocean and began living on land a very long time ago. It seems to be closely related to Wailmer.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon is protected by a layer of thick fat, which halves the damage taken from Fire- and Ice-type moves."
Secondary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in a hailstorm."
Hidden Ability Description: "Removes additional effects to increase the power of moves when attacking."
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon wanders around snowy, icy areas. It protects its body with powerful muscles and a thick layer of fat under its skin.

Primary Ability Description: "Moves can be used on the target regardless of its Abilities."
Hidden Ability Description: "Powers up slicing moves."
Pokedex Entry: When Veluza discards unnecessary flesh, its mind becomes honed and its psychic power increases. The spare flesh has a mild but delicious flavor.

Primary Ability Description: "When attacking, the Pokémon ignores the target Pokémon's stat changes."
Secondary Ability Description: "The Pokémon is oblivious, and that keeps it from being infatuated or falling for taunts."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon is covered with a water veil, which prevents the Pokémon from getting a burn."
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon is a glutton, but it’s bad at getting food. It teams up with a Tatsugiri to catch prey.

Primary Ability Description: "When the Pokémon enters a battle, it goes inside the mouth of an ally Dondozo if one is on the field. The Pokémon then issues commands from there. Dondozo can no longer switch out. Dondozo's stats all raise by 2 stages."
Hidden Ability Description: "Draws in all Water-type moves. Instead of being hit by Water-type moves, it boosts its Sp. Atk."
Pokedex Entry: This is a small dragon Pokémon. It lives inside the mouth of Dondozo to protect itself from enemies on the outside.

Primary Ability Description: "When the Pokémon enters a battle, it goes inside the mouth of an ally Dondozo if one is on the field. The Pokémon then issues commands from there. Dondozo can no longer switch out. Dondozo's stats all raise by 2 stages."
Hidden Ability Description: "Draws in all Water-type moves. Instead of being hit by Water-type moves, it boosts its Sp. Atk."
