Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon is full of vitality, and that prevents it from falling asleep."
Secondary Ability Description: "The Pokémon's intensely focused, and that protects the Pokémon from flinching."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat sharply when its stats are lowered."
Pokedex Entry: When its anger rose beyond a critical point, this Pokémon gained power that is unfettered by the limits of its physical body.

Primary Ability Description: "Contact with the Pokémon may poison the attacker."
Secondary Ability Description: "Restores HP if hit by a Water-type move instead of taking damage."
Hidden Ability Description: "When attacking, the Pokémon ignores the target Pokémon's stat changes."
Pokedex Entry: When attacked, this Pokémon will retaliate by sticking thick spines out from its body. It’s a risky move that puts everything on the line.

Primary Ability Description: "When the Pokémon eats a Berry, it will eat it one more time at the end of the next turn."
Secondary Ability Description: "Prevents opposing Pokémon from using priority moves against the target."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Attack stat if hit by a Grass-type move instead of taking damage."
Pokedex Entry: Now that the brain waves from the head and tail are synced up, the psychic power of this Pokémon is 10 times stronger than Girafarig’s.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the likelihood of additional effects occurring when attacking."
Secondary Ability Description: "Enables a sure getaway from wild Pokémon."
Hidden Ability Description: "Dark-, Ghost-, and Bug-type moves scare the Pokémon and boost its Speed stat."

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the likelihood of additional effects occurring when attacking."
Secondary Ability Description: "Enables a sure getaway from wild Pokémon."
Hidden Ability Description: "Dark-, Ghost-, and Bug-type moves scare the Pokémon and boost its Speed stat."
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon uses its hard tail to make its nest by boring holes into bedrock deep underground. The nest can reach lengths of over six miles.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat sharply when its stats are lowered."
Secondary Ability Description: "When the Pokémon enters a battle, its Attack and Sp. Atk stats are slightly boosted for each of the allies in its party that have already been defeated."
Hidden Ability Description: "By putting pressure on the opposing Pokémon, it raises their PP usage."
Evolution Details: "After Defeating 3 Wild Bisharp That Are Holding a Leader's Crest"
Pokedex Entry: Only a Bisharp that stands above all others in its vast army can evolve into Kingambit.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat in harsh sunlight or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Sightings of this Pokémon have occurred in recent years. The name Great Tusk was taken from a creature listed in a certain book.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat in harsh sunlight or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: There has been only one reported sighting of this Pokémon. It resembles a mysterious creature depicted in an old expedition journal.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat in harsh sunlight or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It is possible that the creature listed as Brute Bonnet in a certain book could actually be this Pokémon.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat in harsh sunlight or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon has characteristics similar to those of Flutter Mane, a creature mentioned in a certain book.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat in harsh sunlight or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: This mysterious Pokémon has some similarities to a creature that an old book introduced as Slither Wing.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat in harsh sunlight or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: No records exist of this Pokémon being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokémon’s traits match up with a creature shown in an expedition journal.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat on Electric Terrain or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon closely resembles a scientific weapon that a paranormal magazine claimed was sent to this planet by aliens.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat on Electric Terrain or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Its shape is similar to a robot featured in a paranormal magazine article. The robot was said to have been created by an ancient civilization.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat on Electric Terrain or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It is very similar to a cyborg covered exclusively by a paranormal magazine. The cyborg was said to be the modified form of a certain athlete.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat on Electric Terrain or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It resembles a certain Pokémon introduced in a paranormal magazine, described as the offspring of a Hydreigon that fell in love with a robot.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat on Electric Terrain or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon resembles an unknown object described in a paranormal magazine as a UFO sent to observe humanity.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat on Electric Terrain or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It has some similarities to a Pokémon introduced in a dubious magazine as a Tyranitar from one billion years into the future.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Attack stat when the Pokémon is hit by a Fire-type move. The Pokémon also cannot be burned."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon gradually regains HP in a snowstorm."
Pokedex Entry: Frigibax absorbs heat through its dorsal fin and converts the heat into ice energy. The higher the temperature, the more energy Frigibax stores.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Attack stat when the Pokémon is hit by a Fire-type move. The Pokémon also cannot be burned."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon gradually regains HP in a snowstorm."
Pokedex Entry: Arctibax freezes the air around it, protecting its face with an ice mask and turning its dorsal fin into a blade of ice.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Attack stat when the Pokémon is hit by a Fire-type move. The Pokémon also cannot be burned."
Hidden Ability Description: "The Pokémon gradually regains HP in a snowstorm."
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon blasts cryogenic air out from its mouth. This air can instantly freeze even liquid-hot lava.

Primary Ability Description: "Dark-, Ghost-, and Bug-type moves scare the Pokémon and boost its Speed stat."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon was born inside a treasure chest about 1,500 years ago. It sucks the life-force out of scoundrels who try to steal the treasure.

Primary Ability Description: "Enables a sure getaway from wild Pokémon."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon was born inside a treasure chest about 1,500 years ago. It sucks the life-force out of scoundrels who try to steal the treasure.

Primary Ability Description: "A body of pure, solid gold gives the Pokémon full immunity to other Pokémon's status moves."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Its body seems to be made up of 1,000 coins. This Pokémon gets along well with others and is quick to make friends with anybody.

Primary Ability Description: "A body of pure, solid gold gives the Pokémon full immunity to other Pokémon's status moves."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Its body seems to be made up of 1,000 coins. This Pokémon gets along well with others and is quick to make friends with anybody.

Primary Ability Description: "The power of the Pokémon's ruinous wooden tablets lowers the Attack stats of all Pokémon except itself."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: The grudge of a person punished for writing the king’s evil deeds upon wooden tablets has clad itself in dead leaves to become a Pokémon.

Primary Ability Description: "The power of the Pokémon's ruinous sword lowers the Defense stats of all Pokémon except itself."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon can control 100 tons of fallen snow. It plays around innocently by leaping in and out of avalanches it has caused.

Primary Ability Description: "The power of the Pokémon's ruinous vessel lowers the Sp. Atk stats of all Pokémon except itself."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: The fear poured into an ancient ritual vessel has clad itself in rocks and dirt to become a Pokémon.

Primary Ability Description: "The power of the Pokémon's ruinous beads lowers the Sp. Def stats of all Pokémon except itself."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It controls flames burning at over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit. It casually swims through the sea of lava it creates by melting rock and sand.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat in harsh sunlight or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It is possible that this is the creature listed as Roaring Moon in an expedition journal that still holds many mysteries.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat on Electric Terrain or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It has some similarities to a mad scientist’s invention covered in a paranormal magazine.

Primary Ability Description: "Turns the sunlight harsh when the Pokémon enters a battle. The ancient pulse thrumming through the Pokémon also boosts its Attack stat in harsh sunlight."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: This seems to be the Winged King mentioned in an old expedition journal. It was said to have split the land with its bare fists.

Primary Ability Description: "Turns the ground into Electric Terrain when the Pokémon enters a battle. The futuristic engine within the Pokémon also boosts its Sp. Atk stat on Electric Terrain."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Much remains unknown about this creature. It resembles Cyclizar, but it is far more ruthless and powerful.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat in harsh sunlight or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: This ferocious creature is shrouded in mystery. It's named after an aquatic monster mentioned in an old expedition journal.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat on Electric Terrain or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Many of its physical characteristics match those of a Virizion from the future that was covered in a paranormal magazine.

Primary Ability Description: "The scent of the Pokemon's syrup spreads across the battlefield, lowering the evasiveness of opposing Pokémon."
Secondary Ability Description: "Makes the Pokémon eat a held Berry when its HP drops to half or less, which is sooner than usual."
Hidden Ability Description: "Items held by the Pokémon are stuck fast and cannot be removed by other Pokémon."
Pokedex Entry: Dipplin is two creatures in one Pokémon. Its evolution was triggered by a special apple grown only in one place.

Primary Ability Description: "Restores allies HP upon entering battle."
Hidden Ability Description: "The heatproof body of the Pokémon halves the damage from Fire-type moves that hit it."
Pokedex Entry: Supposedly, the regrets of a tea ceremony master who died before perfecting his craft lingered in some matcha and became a Pokémon.

Primary Ability Description: "Restores allies HP upon entering battle."
Hidden Ability Description: "The heatproof body of the Pokémon halves the damage from Fire-type moves that hit it."

Hidden Ability Description: "The heatproof body of the Pokémon halves the damage from Fire-type moves that hit it."
Pokedex Entry: It pretends to be tea, trying to fool people into drinking it so it can drain their life-force. Its ruse is generally unsuccessful.

Primary Ability Description: "Restores allies HP upon entering battle."
Hidden Ability Description: "The heatproof body of the Pokémon halves the damage from Fire-type moves that hit it."
Pokedex Entry: It pretends to be tea, trying to fool people into drinking it so it can drain their life-force. Its ruse is generally unsuccessful.

Primary Ability Description: "May badly poison the opponent when the user lands a move against them."
Hidden Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat if intimidated. Moves and items that would force the Pokémon to switch out also fail to work."
Pokedex Entry: After all its muscles were stimulated by the toxic chain around its neck, Okidogi transformed and gained a powerful physique.

Primary Ability Description: "May badly poison the opponent when the user lands a move against them."
Hidden Ability Description: "When it enters a battle, the Pokémon can check an opposing Pokémon's held item."
Pokedex Entry: The chain is made from toxins that enhance capabilities. It stimulated Munkidori's brain and caused the Pokémon's psychic powers to bloom.

Primary Ability Description: "May badly poison the opponent when the user lands a move against them."
Hidden Ability Description: "Powers up the Pokémon's weaker moves."
Pokedex Entry: Fezandipiti owes its beautiful looks and lovely voice to the toxic stimulants emanating from the chain wrapped around its body.

Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: This Pokémon's type changes based on which mask it's wearing. It confounds its enemies with nimble movements and kicks.

Pokedex Entry: It gathers static electricity from its surroundings. The beams it launches when down on all fours are tremendously powerful.

Secondary Ability Description: "Restores a little HP when withdrawn from battle."
Hidden Ability Description: "Items held by the Pokémon are stuck fast and cannot be removed by other Pokémon."
Pokedex Entry: Seven syrpents live inside an apple made of syrup. The syrpent in the center is the commander.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat in harsh sunlight or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: There are scant few reports of this creature being sighted. One short video shows it rampaging and spouting pillars of flame.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat in harsh sunlight or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It's said to incinerate everything around it with lightning launched from its fur. Very little is known about this creature.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat on Electric Terrain or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It resembles a Pokémon described in a dubious magazine as a Terrakion that had been modified by an evil organization.

Primary Ability Description: "Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat on Electric Terrain or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It resembles a mysterious object introduced in a paranormal magazine as a cutting-edge weapon shaped like a Cobalion.

Primary Ability Description: "When Terapagos changes into its Stellar Form, it uses its hidden powers to eliminate all effects of weather and terrain, reducing them to zero."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Terapagos protects itself using its power to transform energy into hard crystals. This Pokémon is the source of the Terastal phenomenon.

Primary Ability Description: "When the Pokémon enters a battle, it absorbs the energy around itself and transforms into its Terastal Form."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Terapagos protects itself using its power to transform energy into hard crystals. This Pokémon is the source of the Terastal phenomenon.

Primary Ability Description: "The Pokémon's shell contains the powers of each type. All damage-dealing moves that hit the Pokémon when its HP is full will not be very effective."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: Terapagos protects itself using its power to transform energy into hard crystals. This Pokémon is the source of the Terastal phenomenon.

Primary Ability Description: "Pokémon poisoned by Pecharunt's moves will also become confused."
Hidden Ability Description: NULL
Pokedex Entry: It feeds others toxic mochi that draw out desires and capabilities. Those who eat the mochi fall under Pecharunt’s control, chained to its will.
